Normangee ISD 6-12
August 7 at 8:28 PM ·

Parents and Students,

6-12 grade schedules can now be viewed through Parent Portal. If you have a question about your schedule, please email Mrs. Tesch at ktesch@normangeeisd.org.

9-12 grade students: The number one goal is to make sure your child is taking the required classes to meet graduation requirements. With so many students choosing different courses, it's very common to have conflicts with preferred electives. If your child was placed in an elective they do not want to take, please email Mrs. Tesch requesting to change it. She will be able to accommodate as much as the schedule allows.

While logged into parent portal, be sure to complete your registration.

Thank you!!

Ms. Williams or another employee will be sitting at the front desk and will take your device and give you a receipt for your records.

post_text:
Graduation Update –

Graduation will be held at Panther Stadium on Friday, May 29th at 7 p.m. Seniors have been given 10 tickets to distribute to their guests. In order to attend graduation in person, you must have a ticket and sit in your assigned location. All guests will need to enter the NISD campus from the OSR entrance near the baseball fields. Graduation will be streamed on the Normangee ISD 6-12 Facebook page and a recording will be posted afterwards.

Rainout Information –

If we are unable to hold graduation on Friday, we will hold it Saturday at 10 am. If the 10 am ceremony is rained out, we will hold it Saturday evening at 7 p.m.

post_text:
Did you know that this week is NISD Staff Appreciation Week? Let's show our staff some love this week!

5/5 Tuesday: Share the Love!
Create a post on social media telling the world how great your teacher is. Be sure and tag them and include #pantherslearning

5/7 Thursday: Show the Love!
Perform a random act of kindness in honor of your teacher or favorite staff member. Send information about what you did to your teacher or create a social media post and tag them. Be sure to include #pantherslearning

5/8 Friday: Spread the Love:
We are having a parade to show our teachers how much we love them! Decorate your car and load up the family. Be at the school at 10:30 am (you must remain in your car). Our teachers will be along main street to watch us spread the love. This will be so much fun! Please let us know in the comments if you plan on participating.

Normangee ISD 6-12
May 4 at 2:33 AM ·

Below are several important reminders and dates for high school students.

May 12th will be the last day of school.

Students who received paper packets each week will need to bring those to the school for drop off on May 11th and May 12th.

All online assignments must be completed by May 12th, as well.

High School lockers have been cleaned out. Students who had lockers may come pick up your bag tomorrow, May 4th, from 9 until 12.

The commissioner is speaking on May 5th about graduation and Covid 19 restrictions. We will finalize our graduation plans and get that out in a timely manner after his speech.

We miss our Panthers! Please stay safe!

post_text:
Parents and Guardians,

The last day of school has been changed. Instead of ending school on May 22nd, the last day of school will be May 12th. We have unused days available in our school calendar that will allow us to meet all requirements by the State of Texas and end school on May 12th. We understand that the last few weeks have been stressful and have provided challenges. Our hope is that this decision allows students and families the opportunity to begin their summer and further minimize any stress associated with these trying times we have been facing.

This means that May 6th will be the last day that meals are provided. This does not affect or impact any other plans regarding the end of the school year. No other dates or plans have been changed.

You will hear plans soon about the last week of school and how we will collect student work and close out the school year.

As always, thank you for your patience.

Parents and Guardians,
We are still without electricity at campus and do not expect it to be restored until later this afternoon. We will NOT be dismissing early. You are free to come check out your student, please know that normal check-out procedures apply.

Normangee ISD Meet the Teacher will be on Monday, August 12th from 4:30 until 6:30. Please come by and meet your teachers and get the 2019-2020 School Year off to a great start! There will also be a meeting for all student-athletes and parents at 5:30. You may also pick up your middle school and high school student’s schedule on Monday.

We will have computers set up for all students who are needing to complete their registration.

Normangee ISD Meet the Teacher will be on Monday, August 12th from 4:30 until 6:30. Please come by and meet your teachers and get the 2019-2020 School Year off to a great start! There will also be a meeting for all student-athletes and parents at 5:30. You may also pick up your middle school and high school student’s schedule on Monday.

post_text: Day 1 of online registration is in the books. We did encounter some challenges, but believe those have been worked out. There are 3-4 forms for each campus that must be printed and completed. If you do not have access to a printer, we have forms printed at the school. Additionally, we have computers available at the school for your use and will be happy to assist you any way we can. New student registration will not be finalized/accepted until all of the required documentation has been turned in to their campus. Thank you for your patience as we make this change.

post_text:
NISD Community,
Effective tomorrow, January 23rd, ALL VISITORS entering the campus MUST HAVE A GOVERNMENT ISSUED ID. To further ensure the safety and security of our students, Normangee ISD has installed the RAPTOR, visitor management system.

This system will allow us to do the following:
1 - Accurately keep a log of who is on campus and why
2 - Instantly screens visitors for previous offenses that would prohibit them from being admitted to campus
3 - Instantly screens for other issues such as custodial conflicts

Please watch the following video that explains a little more how the RAPTOR system works: https://safeYouTube.net/w/CExh

post_text:
Congratulations to the Normangee Tennis Team today as they competed in District 26-AA in Somerville. The Normangee Lady Panthers took District Champions, and the Boys are the Runners-up. Advancing to Regionals are Brianna Day (1st Place Girls Singles), Ethan DeLaGarza (2nd Place Boys Singles), Becky Bouldin and Jordan Ruffeno (2nd Place Girls Doubles), and Madison Light and Mason Woith (1st Place Mixed Doubles).
Becky Rector and Hayden Biddle finished 3rd in Mixed Doubles, Kaylee Morton and Angelica Aguilar finished 3rd in Girls Doubles, Cavan Nichols took 3rd in Boys Singles and Makinzy Pool took 3rd in Girls Singles, Anthony Banda and CJ Rosales (not pictured) took 3rd in Boys Doubles. Thank you Coach Tami Dean!
text:
Congratulations to the Normangee Tennis Team today as they competed in District 26-AA in Somerville. The Normangee Lady Panthers took District Champions, and the Boys are the Runners-up. Advancing to Regionals are Brianna Day (1st Place Girls Singles), Ethan DeLaGarza (2nd Place Boys Singles), Becky Bouldin and Jordan Ruffeno (2nd Place Girls Doubles), and Madison Light and Mason Woith (1st Place Mixed Doubles).
Becky Rector and Hayden Biddle finished 3rd in Mixed Doubles, Kaylee Morton and Angelica Aguilar finished 3rd in Girls Doubles, Cavan Nichols took 3rd in Boys Singles and Makinzy Pool took 3rd in Girls Singles, Anthony Banda and CJ Rosales (not pictured) took 3rd in Boys Doubles. Thank you Coach Tami Dean!
